Jeffrey Sachs, an economics 
professor at Columbia University, talks about the European debt 
crisis, the U.S. economy and imbalances in global living 
standards.  He speaks with Tom Keene and Christine Harper on Bloomberg 
Television's "Surveillance Midday." (Source: Bloomberg)  Running time 17:16
 